messageBody:
Which dot patterns are easiest to recognise, is there a list anywhere?

Has anyone been doing anything with the Quikscript Unicode mapping?
I have some free time over Christmas, I'd be happy to do some work on it
again.

tim_rice09 wrote:
>
> Braille with a Quickscript concept is a great idea. Braille users
> suffer just the same or more from cumbersome spellings. A better idea
> than using Quickscript shapes in the cells is using the letter
> frequency chart to assign the most common letters to the easiest to
> recognize dot patterns.
> For example: Braille cell A would be assigned to Utter, &&&.
>
>
